@@TJvTipOfDayOption.toShowOnStartUp
Specifies whether the checkbox on the dialog is checked or unchecked. Also, if no <LINK
TJvTipOfDay.OnCanShow, OnCanShow> event handler is used, it determines whether the dialog is shown on startup of the application.

Use flag toShowOnStartUp before calling <LINK TJvTipOfDay.Execute, Execute>, to specify whether the checkbox must be checked or unchecked. Use flag toShowOnStartUp after calling <LINK
TJvTipOfDay.Execute, Execute>, to determine whether the checkbox was checked or unchecked when the user closed the dialog.

